I think I got all the issues. I elected to disable use_multiprocessing tests on windows for now. But maybe we can add checks into the code itself for use_multiprocessing, on windows?

Anyway, the PR is out for review, I also enabled python/keras tests for cmake build, we should see if I was really able to catch all failures.
